35 SUMMARY
3366 This resolution proposes to amend the Constitution of Maine to prohibit any new taxes
3377 and increases in taxes, including taxes on income and property, increases in fiscal spending
3388 beyond the rate of inflation and increases in debt unless those taxes or increases are
3399 approved by the voters of the State or by the voters in the municipality or county affected
4400 by the tax, fiscal spending or debt, as determined by and in accordance with a process
4411 enacted by the Legislature in statute.
